 competing\nmodels like modified gravity, thus weakening any detectable cosmological\nsignal. Given the ubiquitous presence of a neutrino background, these effects\nhave to be taken into account in future missions aimed at constraining the\nproperties of the \"Dark\" components of the Universe.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 22 Sep 2014 20:00:14 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 18 Dec 2014 13:51:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-22"}
